 <song> 
<title>156 HOWARD</title>
<lyrics>[V1]
 WHEN all Thy mercies, blessed God,
 Each rising soul surveys, 
 Transported with the view, we're lost
 In wonder, love and praise.
[V2]
 Unnumbered comforts on each soul 
 Thy tender care bestowed,
 Before our infant hearts conceived 
 From whom those comforts flowed.
[V3]
 Ten thousand thousand precious gifts 
 Our daily thanks employ,
 But oh! Thy greatest gift, Thy Son, 
 This is our greatest joy.
[V4]
 Through all eternity to Thee
 A joyful song we'll raise, 
 But e'en eternity's too short
 To utter all Thy praise.
</lyrics>
